FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773993882
OL,3,CMan 'deeply upset' after parents'
OL,4,Cgravestone is cordoned off at cemetery
OL,6,FGabriele is responsible for his
OL,7,Fparent's gravestone and is happy to
OL,8,Fpay for repairs - but before he can do
OL,9,Fthat - he'll need to pay the council a
OL,10,F#78 fee before any work can begin.
OL,12,FHe wants to pay, but argues the
OL,13,Fborough council needs to waive the
OL,14,Fadmin fee in order to help him and
OL,15,Fothers with the cost.
OL,17,FMr Scicluna says the nearby cemetery
OL,18,Fin Mays Lane in Earley does not charge
OL,19,Ffor paperwork, or for any tradesmen to
OL,20,Fgo on site to do repairs on the graves.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773993882
OL,3,CMan 'deeply upset' after parents'
OL,4,Cgravestone is cordoned off at cemetery
OL,6,F"It's not just myself its other people
OL,7,FI'm doing this for as well," he said.
OL,9,F"Other people I've spoken to around
OL,10,Fhere feel very strongly about this."
OL,12,FA spokesperson for Reading Borough
OL,13,FCouncil said: "While we appreciate
OL,14,Fadditional costs are never welcome,
OL,15,Fespecially as a result of bereavement,
OL,16,Fthe Council does have a duty to ensure
OL,17,Fthe safety of all visitors to the
OL,18,Fcemetery grounds.
OL,26,@uD@OOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
